{
  "info": {
    "name": "Athena Plugins API",
    "description": "Test collection for the plugin management lifecycle: list, get, enable, disable, settings, and contract-shape validation.\n\n## Lifecycle Covered\n\n1. **List plugins** — enumerate installed plugins\n2. **List available** — discover available plugins from registry\n3. **Get plugin** — retrieve specific plugin by name\n4. **Get settings** — read registered and public settings\n5. **Update settings** — change plugin configuration via PeerTube-compatible route\n6. **Enable/Disable** — toggle plugin status\n7. **Install contract** — validate install-from-URL request shape (may fail if URL unreachable)\n8. **Uninstall** — remove a plugin\n9. **Error cases** — auth failures and invalid inputs\n\n## Scope Note\n\nInstall-from-URL and Upload-plugin require a real plugin archive. These requests are included for API contract validation (response shape, auth, error codes) but may return 4xx if no archive is available in the test environment. Use the 'contract-only' tests to validate the API surface.\n\n## Environment Variables Required\n\n- `baseUrl` - API base URL\n- `access_token` - Admin JWT access token\n\n## Variables Set During Run\n\n- `plugin_npm_name` - Name of the plugin to test lifecycle operations on",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Plugin Discovery",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List Plugins",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.equal(200);",
                  "});",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Response has data envelope', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(body.success).to.be.true;",
                  "  pm.expect(body).to.have.property('data');",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Data is array', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(Array.isArray(body.data) || (body.data && Array.isArray(body.data.data))).to.be.true;",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}", "type": "text" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/plugins",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "plugins"]
            },
            "description": "List all installed plugins. Requires admin or mod role."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "List Available Plugins",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.equal(200);",
                  "});",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Success flag present', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(body).to.have.property('success');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}", "type": "text" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/plugins/available",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "plugins", "available"]
            },
            "description": "List plugins available from the registry."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Plugin by Name",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "// Set a plugin name - use one that exists in the system or expect 404",
                  "const name = pm.environment.get('plugin_npm_name') || 'peertube-plugin-hello-world';",
                  "pm.environment.set('plugin_npm_name', name);"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200 or 404', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect([200, 404]).to.include(pm.response.code);",
                  "});",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.test('Plugin data structure', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(body.success).to.be.true;",
                  "    pm.expect(body.data).to.have.property('name');",
                  "    pm.expect(body.data).to.have.property('version');",
                  "    pm.expect(body.data).to.have.property('status');",
                  "  });",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}", "type": "text" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/plugins/{{plugin_npm_name}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "plugins", "{{plugin_npm_name}}"]
            },
            "description": "Get a specific plugin by its npm name."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
